\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can I have your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Mary Alice - Morris.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 39 Parton Grove, Weston Coyney.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you are a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You've been married twice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me the year of your first marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And the year of your second marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 1929.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 1899, September the twenty - twenty-ninth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Wood Street, but not - the number I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's Longton isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me for how many years you lived in this house in Wood Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well I can't tell you because I was born there. And believe me - from there I've - I found out recent - afterwards - we must have had about eight houses. Up to when I was five. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You can't remember any of them particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The only one I can remember is down near - Nook. Down Heathcote Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
I wouldn't be able to tell you off hand, I was only five. All the time - all that I knew as - there come two police to the door. That's what 
made me - waken up then, you know, how things come to children. And it was dark night and - when they came in they were after me auntie. Me auntie didn't pay her rates. She lived up Dresden. So the police, there was one back and one front. And that's when
 I first realized what poverty was, you know. I'd never wakened up to it - to the hardships until then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This was when you were about five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When I was five, yes, the police came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 After your auntie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They took her away to prison.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because she hadn't paid her rates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you remember why the family made all these moves, why you moved so often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes I can. They wouldn't pay the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They wouldn't or they couldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They wouldn't. They wouldn't - no idea of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was this your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
My father and my mother as well, she was as bad. Because you know there was empty houses, hundreds of them. That's all you've got to do, go and give 'em sixpence for - a key. 'Cos one of the neighbours had the 
keys. You gave her sixpence, that was it. They'd give you a key - And
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you just moved in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right, yes. Oh yes, all that was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So they knocked about because they didn't want to pay the rent?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Didn't want to pay it. That's 
right. After a fair bit they would have been turned out. So when we'd been in so long and we didn't pay any rent - they got made to move. We never dared have a fire on the Mondays when the - the landlord was round. We didn't. No. 'Cos - he never knew whic
h house we were in. Be about seven or eight houses and we'd go from one house to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you remember the first house where you actually stayed for any length of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Wellington Court, and I was thirteen then. And that's the only time. I was thirteen then. What do you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you were thirteen before you actually settled down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You were going from house to house all those years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And your parents still refused to pay rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
That's right. Because the old man wouldn't work long enough, or if he did he worked just for a bit of - bread and butter, we never knew what an egg was, only once a year. And that was - Easter Sunday, they were twenty-four for a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So for all these years you had to hop about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because he wouldn't work long enough to pay any rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We were turned out of two or three houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Put out in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. We had that little boy die, it was through th
at you know, that baby boy. 'Cos she was confined and after the ten days they put her out and she was in the coalhouse - in a bed in the coalhouse. That's what made that little baby bad. And it turned T.B.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me how many brothers and sisters you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 There was - three sisters and a brother before me. And there was me Louie and Elsie, Winnie, Nellie and Frankie. The last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Your mother had three daughters and a son before you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 All of whom died in infancy, then there came yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me who came after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Louie. Yes. And then Anna, then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 Winnie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 , then Nellie. And then the little boy, Frank.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When I was born? He'd be thirty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Bolton Place. Bolton Place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where's this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Down New Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In Longton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did he do for a living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well - more or less he was a bricklayer, but he did work in a pit a little bit. You know. What little bit it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And he was on haulage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You said that he did hop from job to job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right, yes. Bricklaying. You know, he wasn't bricklaying, he was labouring.That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Up to the time of the first world war he was in the pit on haulage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Down - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Most of his time would be bricklaying?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember him doing anything before he was a bricklayer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, just a little bit in the pit. On the haulage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about afterwards, what did he do afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well he never did anything - after the war. No. When he - when he came back from the war he didn't do anything at all, he wasn't any -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This is after the 1914-18 war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 1914 - 
1914 war. There wasn't any work about then you know. Wasn't much work at all. And - he just did odd days, you know, labouring. Perhaps two days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did he do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You say he had enough difficulty getting a job anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So of course you remember him being out of work do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh yes. Oh quite a lot. Well - myself, I'm very prejudiced against anybody is - out of work. I - I've got a very bad habit of saying - if they want work they can f
ind it. Well, with me - I'd scrub floors at seventy-two - before I'll be out of work. But - I mean, they're not all like I are. No. The same as I say - the same as I say - if they want some work there is some somewhere. If there isn't then I'd make away w
ith myself. Oh I - I - pride doesn't bother me, I am proud, but only for having - something off anybody. But I wouldn't be too proud to do any kind of work. Oh no, no I wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well she was eight years - younger than me father and he was thirty-six, she'd be twenty-eight, wouldn't she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She came from Arthur Street, in Longton, down by St Praggerty's church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she work before she was married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, she used to work in a scoring shop. What we used to call biscuit warehouse then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I remember her working - a little bit, but - when you come to think she hadn't got much time to work when she had ten children in her t
ime did she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she manage to do any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh dear no. No. You didn't find many women going out work them days you know. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she do anything when the children were growing up, did she ever go back to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. No
, because when we were growing up see was when the war was on. You see, I was fourteen nearly. When we went to live in that house, well when the war broke out I was turned fourteen, I was going to work. Well of course - Louie was only two years in differe
nce, the war was on four years. Well from 1914 to 1917 'til she died was three years. So she had two workers. Mother never went to work. Oh no, she wouldn't get up and do her cleaning. We had to do that at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She stayed in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Reading. Yes, they weren't - weren't like us you know. But - that was only work that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 Louie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 ever did, until me mother died, then she never worked. She's - much like her mother. We was all good workers. Well I say good workers, we're good housewives. But - really 
and truly I'm the only one that has stuck work. I never - I've never failed. The only time I failed when I got a - have a baby, but - and get back again. Just enough to pay the rate and the rent and that was it. But - oh work, oh it's a pleasure. It was a
lways a pleasure to me when it was very hard so now I'm sitting down all day it's - it's easy, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I was going to ask you to tell me about your life at home up until you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And about the house you can remember best, seeing as you lived in so many houses can you give me an idea of what sort of house they were?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well, I can - they were - two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 bed roomed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  houses. I'll you one thought for sure. Five of us used to sleep in one bed. And that was very often the case of families them days you know. Oh yes. But - more or less they were two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 bed roomed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  houses. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What was downstairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Furniture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh - there was a parlour and a - and kitchen. And then a scullery. They used to call them the wash house. Them days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And the usual toilet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Outside in the yard, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brothers and sisters live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. That's one thing they wouldn't do, wouldn't have lodgers. No. No, we couldn't ha
ve lodgers could we, we were always moving. We were always on the move ourselves. Couldn't have lodgers could you? Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 My gosh she didn't, we didn't have enough money for food. Oh dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she do the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Yes, in a bucket. There was four or five of us. Mind she was clean. You can say that, she was clean. But - she'd wash in a - it was like a sink stove then, like shallow. She'd wash the sheets in that and 
- our petticoats and shimmies'd be in the buckets. Used to wash 'em in a bucket. Used to have - a petticoat - we only had one. Petticoat washed Friday night, and our chemise Saturday night. Put 'em on Sunday morning ready go off church. Oh yes, we hadn't 
g
ot nothing to wash. But she was clean. Will say that. She made us - she saw that we did it, you know what I mean. Scrubbing brush and a blacklead brush - it had got to be done the right way as well. And the table was as white as snow. And two chairs, yes.
 Only two chairs for the six of us - seven of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your mother and father make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 My mother used to - make - coats out of jackets. We used to beg jackets and she'd make us - frocks out of them. Frocks. You know, take
 the buttons off and the buttonholes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16536882\charrsid10098272 stitch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  'em up. That was it, it was a frock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were your clothes ever new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never. The only time we had - new was - when would it be - I should think in about seven. And we only had - a new petticoat, white frock, 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16536882\charrsid10098272 Corpus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 Christi basket and slippers and socks. And - me mother used to have 'em on a club cheque. We never had nothing else again. We daren't kneel down when we went to Corpus Christi in case you dirtied 'em, because they had to go pawn shop next day. We
 never saw any 'em again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Until when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The following year when we had all new. That's the only time we ever had a new frock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So where did your clothes come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She used to have a club cheques. Used to get a lot then for twenty-four 
shillings for clothe three of us. The three girls, we used to go - that twenty-four shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 None of the clothes secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, they were all new but she had it off a club cheque. Two }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 bob a}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This is from when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh
 yes, right through that was until - 'til the'14 war come on. Always on Corpus Christi but we daren't - we daren't kneel down. Daren't dirty 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 By God we didn't. No, never. The only pair of new shoes we had was when we had 'em from school. We didn't get them very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So where did your shoes come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We used to go and get secondhand ones from Fanny Dales or - the shop across from Catholic church. You know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 Wilshore's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  in the market now? Her grandmother - used to sell secondhand clothes. Used to go there and get 'em. Always used to go to school in odd shoes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Odd shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Oh yes. As near as you could get 'em you know. There were no lace up, they were button up in them days. If they were laced that
 was it, if they were buttoned that was it. Oh yes. And I've carried our Louie school, through the - through near Dresden to Catholic school on me back you know and she was a big girl. I used to be creased with her, and she'd no shoes at all on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In the cold weather as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes. Yes, on me back. And I used to have pains in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 me side}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 , 'cos she was heavy girl you know. And - I always used to think it was stitch I'd got but it worried me to - I thought since, and then after I thought it was growi
ng pains. But I realized in the later years it was her, it was strain. She was heavy and she was idle you know and she used to lean on me and I was the worrit.You know, I used to worry. I daren't drop her. 'Cos if she told me mother I'd have a good hiding
. And I had to struggle through with her. I did. She's always been the same. Always been lazy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You said she still is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She is, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your father ever help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh by gum he didn't. He wouldn't know which way to do it. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nothing at all, not fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh no, not - decorating, was never no decorating done 'til I was - left - with the kids. There wasn't. Never remembered any decorating being done. The things that was ever done wa
s when - after me mother died, and I started putting me hands together a bit you know. And I decorated, that's when I first started - learnt it. Oh by gum no. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So he didn't do anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no, there was nothing done, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did he ever help with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Oh no, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 He never dressed you or undressed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Bathed you or read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. He didn't. There was only one thing he was there for and that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 to }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 get 'em. Wasn't look after 'e
m. Lord. Was quite a lot I got you know them days. There was. He would never be seen with - I never remembered my mother until the war broke out ever seeing her with a pair of warm shoes on feet. She couldn't get off the doorstep. If she - and when she us
e
d to go church, and it wasn't far to the Catholic church, used to have to buy a pair of shoes to go church - be churched in. Never had anything. They didn't. And you - same as I say - you couldn't do anything with the men them days. Because you'd got no o
ne you could - talk to. Well I mean it was hopeless anybody - kept having kids every - twelve months nearly Couldn't go away could you. Couldn't. Good heavens. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have tasks at home that you had to carry out regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes, we had to do the - mother always saw that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 grate}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 was nicely polished. And the stairs and the bedroom floors had got to be scrubbed. That's why I say she was clean. To the particular part she could be. Oh yes, we only had one sheet on the bed. One over us and one
 under us. Then there was a bed cover and all the others were coats. That we begged. Oh no, I don't think anybody had a harder life than we did, unless it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 gypsies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 . And yet my mother was definitely proud. She'd walk - walk about the house as though she'd got - tons of money. Very stuck up. Oh definite. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your other sisters have things that they had to do regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, it always fell on me - really. Because - I was the tame one. I'd rather make haste and do it. And I never remember mother saying, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 Louie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  you do this and you do the other, it was always, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 M}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 ary Alice. See? Well, Mary Alice did it, because I was petrified, used to have some - terrific good hidings. 'Cos when me mother and me father had been fighting - then I'd be the fi
rst one take it out of after. They didn't ask me do a thing, they told you before you - you get time to do it they were up and - that was it. Yes. But of course the other two little 'uns it didn't fall on them. It was me. I got it, yes. Yes, I got it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How long did you have to carry on helping in the house after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well - let's see - three years. Then the war was on then. Me mother was having a bit of a - good time then you know. But - she never - she never went to work, she used to - have novels and go bed and - didn't get up 'til dinnertimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you had to do all the work in the house because she lay in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. She'd be up at dinnertimes but - we used to go dinner then from work see. You'd go down for your dinner, oh ye
s. But she always went out at nights, old Bridge Inn, didn't go out with anybody, went with the women 'cos war was on you know. Lot of women together, soldiers wives. And - she'd say I want you make me a - some lobby for when I come in tonight, you know. 
J
ust like that. And then more or less if they came in and they brought friends with her and they were drinking and - now you go to bed Alice. I was forty-one bust. I was great big hefty girl. Used to talk to me as though I was just a baby. And she stood at
 
the front gate - talking to the neighbours, which she used - used to do like. You daren't pass her. You'd have to stand there when you come in from work, you'd wait. She'd stand there deliberate. Just to make you know that you'd got to do it. Then she'd s
a
y, you can pass now. And I was seventeen. I was bigger than I am now. Eleven stone nine then. Seventeen. Oh I were forty-one bust. Oh I'm not very heavy now. Then I was. Oh yes. And she'd say - when she come in, off to bed. Used to walk very proud you kno
w
, very abrupt. Never asked you do a thing, always told you. And - you wouldn't dare give a dirty look or anything because these women were coming in like. And the neighbours - boozing. I'd go to bed and I'd only been in bed about half an hour, she'd say, 
M
ary Alice. Come down these stairs. I have to dress and come down you know, 'cos we had no nightdresses. Had - you know, you had to lie in bed with a chemise on at that age. Well I used to lie in bed with me petticoat on. And - she'd say, stand by that doo
r there and sing this sort of thing - for these people. You know, while they were drinking. Used to have to stand there singing. Frozen to death. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember helping the younger children with the things they found difficult, such as eating and dressing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No, they used to have to get theirselves off to school. Mother didn't get 'em ready. She didn't get 'em ready at all, she wouldn't get up. No. She wouldn't get up. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 
And - one morning I was at work, me and Louie was at work and there was Annie and Winnie downstairs, and some - you know, we used to have a saucepan of water on the front of the grate them days - 'cos we hadn't got a kettle, and it tipped over on Winnie. 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She was only a little girl about seven. Six or seven. No, she wouldn't - she'd be about six. And she was scalded all down her face. Yes, she was. That's quite true that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes, we had to go bed early. Yes. In fact me mother'd be in bed early after Tuesdays. Used to 
get paid on a Monday then they'd go out Tuesday. And then they'd be waiting for Saturday for their wages. Go out again. Wednesday, Thursday and Friday never went out. We got paid Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Talking about in your schooldays though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What time did you have to go to bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
We had to go early. Every night nearly. That's when mother and dad were together. Used to have to go about eight o'clock. And I tell you many a time I had to go bed without any tea and they used to let us go v
ery early. And a very particular saying she used to say, if you go to bed you won't feel half so hungry. 'Cos we never had anything to eat hardly. Many's the time I've - filled myself with orange peel. Clean orange - clean orange peel, you know. Used to t
hrow 'em in the gutter then you know, there was no bins or anything about. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Who put you to bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh we - we used to put ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Your mother never put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You say you used to share a bed, can you tell me the sleeping arrangements of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well - I remember when there was me and Louie and Nancy. Nancy was the little one, she slept at the top of the bed, against the wall. And me mother next and me dad next, and then me and Lou were sleeping at the bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 All five of you in one bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes. Yes. Used to sleep at the bottom. Well if we got a bed we wouldn't have enough bedclothes for two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about when there was more of you, when you got this young boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Of course - well we - she bought another bed - another small - well, didn't buy one, had it given her, a little bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was it put into the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Who would sleep in there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Me and Lou slept in it. And then the little kids - in the big bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 With your mum and dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well there was no cots nor nothing them days, not at our house, never saw one. We didn't. Yes. Never had a sofa. Never saw a sofa, it was chair - two chairs and a table. The first time I saw a - a sofa, it wasn't 
a sofa, it was a squab. How old would I be about? Fifteen then. I would. No, we had no furniture. Just that bed upstairs that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We used to bath in front of fire. In a bucket. 'Course - after me mother died - I bought a b
ath tin, 'cos I was in charge then of the kids. 'Cos me father was in the Army. He was still at France when she died you know. And I was left in charge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did she die with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She died with cancer of the bowels. But - they reckoned it was through being kicked. Kicked a lot with him. Used to fight a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They used to fight did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh they did. Good heavens. Oh used to fight like lions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why did they fight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well it was all over drink wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because he used to come in drunk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or because she used to come in drunk as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No. Oh no. He used to come in drunk. Well - if you never got no money for food and your dad drunk - used to go and sub on his - their wages before he'd earned them. Oh they used t
o fight like dogs. Me mother was - Irish you know. Well I - I was myself. You know - when I'd got to I could fight. And fight hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It sounds as though you had to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I had to do. Well it put her in her grave anyhow. She died when she was forty-thr
ee. And that was through being kicked. He wrote it in. The cancer was through being kicked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So he was a very nasty man really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, oh yes he was. No doubt about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me how often you did bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Every week. Yes. Every Sat
urday night. Because we always prepared for church. That had to come number one. Sunday morning. Wouldn't be allowed to stop at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Couldn't miss it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me when you had clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh every week, we ju
st used to wash one out. Until - I left school. Then she used - them she bought a tub, when I left school like and was working. She bought a tub and she used to wash in the tub. But she was a rice washer. I think she was a woman that was spoiled. I do. I 
think she was very affectionate - to me father in her way, and then when he used to treat her so bad she was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
. I think I am apt to be like that as well. You know, do anything for 'em. And then when they've rubbed it in that far - and it starts to - hurt. And that's it. That's how it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where did we eat? - On the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In which room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 There was only one room then you know. More or less. We never used no parlours. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nothing in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no, no. There wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you used to eat in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did your mother cook with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh - perhaps - two saucepans and a kettle, that's all - oh, and a frying pan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she cook on the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
We had range - oh it was all fire. Yes. It was very rare - I ever saw her do any frying. But - more or less that came - later on in life, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well before you went to school. Got your own. Oh I used to cut it for 'em, two rounds of bread and butter. Very - very often we didn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You didn't eat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 My God we did, very often. We did, we had nothing, many, many, many a morning. My God we didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about your father, did he have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well if he - if he was going to work he'd have - some bread and butter before he went. Or more or less sometimes there'd be a jar of jam, you get two pound jar then for fourpence ha'penny. That was a - that was a luxury. As I told you we 
never knew what it was have an egg only once a year. That was Easter Sunday. You couldn't - we waited for Easter Sunday like you do now for Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you drink in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have a drink every morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or did you ever go without?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no, we went without a lot. No, went without very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So there were times when you actually went to school without anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh we had nothing. Oh yes. Oh definite, yes. But - they used to give you m
eals you know at school. Used to go up - you know where the ice cream shop is now, Lewis'? Well it used to be - grocers and - grocers and confectionist. And children - that they knew weren't having enough food, they used to send 'em up there and give'em b
read and jam them days. And I don't know why but - I was - I've been as fit as a fiddly all my life. Though we never had a great lot of food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your father ever go out without breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well he used to have a piece of toast. Just a piece of to
ast before they went to work. As near as I can remember. There wouldn't be no - no bacon or nothing of that. No. No, he never had much - really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have breakfast on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We always had a Sunday dinner. Now that's funny isn't it? Sunday morning we had toast, you know. But - we always had a Sunday dinner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What sort of things did you have for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh good heavens. Mother used to have a - a shilling dinner. That was a - a rabbit, five pound of potatoes - two pound of carrots, no,
 one pound of carrots and one pound of parsnips and - packet of sage - all for a shilling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Would that feed the lot of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Yes. A real good dinner, good Sunday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was that regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes, we had a good Sunday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about your midday meals, what did you call your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you have for dinner in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well to be truthful - we had just anything we could clap our hands on. Sometimes me mother'd get - some bacon bones. Y
ou could get a - a load for a penny you know. And a - ha'penny onion, ha'penny carrot, got a good meal. There was plenty of - bacon on the bones so - the broth was gorgeous, it was, really gorgeous. And peas they used to put in sometimes. Damn good meal, 
b
ut - then perhaps - if - we'd go anything at all, any coppers at all we'd have some bacon dish. It was already sliced, it was better bacon than you get today you know. It was. About sixpence a pound. Half a pound of that with a little tin of tomatoes, we 
used to have to have our - bread dipped you know and that was it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh, that was jam. Jam - oh no, never had nothing else. I never ever noticed anything, only - as we got a little bit older we had - custard. It was only a penny. Pint of milk a penny. Custard and bread and better for Sunday tea. It was more - other people 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 besides}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 us like that you know. There was. But the only difference was some parents'd try to get more, and make more of a dish up, and others, you know, were too - to lazy I think myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Your parents were too lazy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh yes. They were - they were too lazy. Well must have been lazy else they'd have gone out and got something for us wouldn't they. And there was nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So they didn't eat either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no, they didn't have no different than us. No. I once knew a time when - well, many a time, when we asked a quarter of bacon, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  ha'pence. And a quarter of cheese. And you can imagine what that went like. It went on one big plat
e, tin plate. And me dad used to give us all a little piece of it. You know. He wouldn't sit and eat it himself. Was just a round but there was only a little tiny bit on it you know. But - that was when it was - a meal. Them days when we had a little bit 
of something, but there was many a day we didn't have anything duck.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You'd go the whole day without eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We have. We have. I mean if you hadn't had any wages there'd be no money coming in often. And there's very often in winter time that woul
dn't work in a pit. Don't think he liked pit work. And - you couldn't - you couldn't condemn a man for being frightened of pit could you? Not really. Well then in the - in the wintertime there was no labouring going on, there wasn't much building. The onl
y
 building more or less then days was the repairs of ovens or kilns or pot banks. See? And he used to go scouting round for that. They weren't big master builders. They were only local men like, with a couple of brickies used to call 'em. One bricky and tw
o
 labourers. And many a time when he used to get this - these odd jobs, before he's started he's all - he's had to sub on his wages. Yes. Yes. He used to say, can I - can you sub me two shilling, for some food like to start off? Oh yes, that happened very 
o
ften. I know I used to walk from the bottom of New Street right up to - the Tam o' Shanta, up Mellacote Road for this two shilling, you know, for - to - a man named - called Jim Mann. I often think about him. When I go down that way. Yes, it's - all we go
t
. The best job I ever knew him to have any length of time was Turners garage. Do you know where that is? Well - Devonshire Road. That big garage. Well it was Turners then. They had it built. That was the most work I ever known him do. You know. Keep going
 on to it. Otherwise it would have been two or three days a week perhaps and then finished. So there's no - surety of our food. No surety whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember your mother baking her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, but I - I do remember her making - pota
to cakes one - one Christmas. With plain flour and - potatoes, you know, all mashed up together. Mind I didn't like 'em. And - I have known her occasionally to - make seed cake. That was only one, I couldn't eat it. No, I couldn't eat it. I've been hungry
 and I've tried many a time, taken the seeds out but there was too many. I couldn't eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she ever make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You must be joking. Good heavens, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. Good heavens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she ever make any medicines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or brew any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No. No, I don't think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she ever try to grow any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no, good heavens. It was never mentioned. No I think we were about - the low
est of the people of - there was - hundreds like us you know. But I think we were in a low grade, them days. Well - if a mother and father don't pull together, that's it, isn't it? No doubt about it. You've got to pull.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you remember how many times a week you did actually eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Meat? Once. And that was Sunday. Oh yes. Sometimes - might manage a - a cows heart, because a lot of meat in that. But they were only ninepence. And that'd be us through for three days, there was such a lot in - big
 things. Sometimes we used to have that. As I tell you we had a Sunday dinner. Little as it was. You know. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember seeing - your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No, I don't think so. No, I don't think so. I think - myself, she was as eager for food as we were and then that was it, you couldn't - you couldn't push back. Couldn't push back no further in my family 'cos we had nothing hardly. But - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you actually had a meal were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Very strict. Very strict - me mother was. Me dad not - not so much but - me mother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever leave anything on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never, we didn't. There was only one plate. We had one plate only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You all had to eat off the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, we didn't eat off the one, it was put on your bread. See? Something you don't know anything about isn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 If
 there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask for it to be given to you or did you have to wait until your mother offered it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well wouldn't have to ask. If there was anything. It's all shared up. And everybody alik
e. 'Cos she knew we really - needed it. And - I never knew any of us being out of - place. Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We didn't have a knife and fork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not even for Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, we had just a spoon. No, we didn't. Hadn't got no knives and forks. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Could you ever take books or toys to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, I never saw any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You didn't have toys and books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well to be tr
uthful - we couldn't be against the table much, 'cos we were standing. See, and as soon as you'd eaten the first thing you do it go away don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You only had two chairs didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you went to the table did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You just went to the table when it was ready?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your mother always serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How would the younger children manage for their meals before they could go to the table themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well mother'd - give it to 'em on her knee wouldn't she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She wasn't a person you could get across. You couldn't talk her round or anything. And s
he wasn't a conversationalist with children. She hadn't got time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she ever show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, I don't think so. No - she - she was more regimental.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Suppose you had any worries, could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I suppose as we got older she'd have lived we would. Would have done, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But not while you were youngsters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, he was fairly easy, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was he an affectionate man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 With us children
, yes, but he wasn't with my mother. No. Me mother - thought a lot about him. But - never saw my father return any. No. But he was very easy with children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Could you share your worries with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 More so than your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, but
 you wouldn't dare to. No. You wouldn't dare to. She wasn't a woman who - if - we'll say if you did anything like kids do, you never hear - hear repeated - wait 'til your father comes. She was the boss. As regards giving us the punishment and that. She wa
s a - a real - we had loads of good hidings - for nothing. Things that you might say today. Nothing whatever. But I - I - always - put that down to poverty. Lot of it was you know. Poverty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh they expected the best out of you. Well to be truthful I was frightened of her. My mother. I was - terribly frightened of her. That's a funny thing that is but - I wouldn't - I've been a very strict mother, but not in that regimental style. No. I didn'
t look for things same as my mother did. But same as I say I think that was a kind of a get out to express her feelings. What she was going through. Of course we didn't realize that then, not as kids. No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Yes. She - we were very disciplined. No doubt about it. She was the boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did they say you should hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. If anything - happened, if her back was turned and we did anyt
hing - she wouldn't give one good hiding, she'd give all but-the baby. She'd say, who's done that, but one wouldn't give the other away. So the result was that we all had a good hiding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about if a child in the street hit you, could you hit that child back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes, always made to stand on your own two feet. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well they'd expect me - I think they'd expect us to be - me - me mother especially, she was very 
proud. And - she always used to say, you hold your head up. And - if you did sit down at the table anytime - those shoulders back. You know. She was very keen in her way. And I think if she'd have had the chance - to bring us up in a proper manner, she wo
uld have been a good mother. You know what I mean? And I think she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Had times not been so hard you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
She pulled - she was pulled right down and she got all the - I think she got all the matter taken out of it. All the glamour of the life, yo
u know. She didn't look forward to anything nice from a child, she was always looking to see what they were going to do, see. She got no outlook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well - they used to bloody. But nothing any more. But - me mother didn't - swear a great deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did they think if you swore?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Us? We daren't, you mustn't say that, oh Good Lord. Oh no, there was nothing like that. No. No, nothing like that at our house. No. It never approached us. It didn't when we grew up. Didn't approach us at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 If grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 My word you weren't. We weren't - you weren't allowed passed them if they were talking. No.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You were saying if your mother was standing at the gate you had to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, and I was seventeen then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We'd have a darned good hiding, we'd deserve one wouldn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Who would give the good hiding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Only me mother. Me father - never did. He always used to say, you can do enough for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So he never had occasion to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. He wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you were smacked were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh, smacked wasn't the word. My mother was very heavy. Punching you know. Oh yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 With her fist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh yes. Definite, yes. She hit you and you could - feel it. Oh never - she made no bones about it, if you did wrong you had got to pay for it. That was - and I think that's how it should be. I do today, I think that's the trouble wit
h kids, they've got no fear in them. I reckon a child brought up with a certain amount of fear - makes a better citizen than - the one that's coddled. And accepts - want everything to go their way. They want everything what they think. Whether it's good, 
bad or indifferent. Well we weren't brought up like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You don't think you're any a worse person for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No indeed, no, I don't. No, and I've been very strict with my children. I know - the reason I was more strict was I hadn't got time - to -
 go right detail down into things, because I was - off at work in the morning half past seven. And them days you didn't get home 'til after six. And when you got four - and when you've got four children - the trouble is you haven't got time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Yes I do. Very - very - whatsit. I remember me mother making us a - a jacket. Making a - a frock out of a jacket. Now I didn't know then, but I know after like, that she was big in pregnancy. Of
 course them days you didn't see that. You didn't see - imagine - you didn't notice your mother's tummy. Because it was never dawned on, it was never taught to you, you didn't realize things. And - it appears my father was out - he'd been at work and was 
o
ut drinking and hadn't come home with any wages. Saturday you know. And - of course the pubs were open all day then. And - she - called me in for something and - whatever I'd done, I'd forgot what it was, but I know she - beat me and she ripped this jack 
-
 this coat - off my back in shreds and threw it on the floor and left me standing there. Out - and - I think it was out of - passion to think that she'd sat - and got to make a coat - frock out of a jacket, to cover me, and he could stop out with his wage
s. So the result was she - took it out of me that I'd done something wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You can't remember what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I just don't know, I - I think it was - I was running along the wall at the back. Very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And she was so }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7999938\charrsid10098272 incensed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  because of your father's behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. It was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you feel about being punished like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well, I was used to it. The only difference was I was - terrified of doing anything wrong. But if I thought I was going to do - do wrong you know. But - for running along the wall like that, which is only natural for a girl about eight wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It was hard punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 To do. I got punished for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents, 
or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Me mother played it. Yes. No, me father wasn't interested really. And I think that's where a lot of it came in because - if he'd have shown some affection - you know. He didn't come down to earth 
as - as a husband and father. And I think that's what me mother wanted. I think she couldn't get - understand him. Myself. And - the truth of it is - I don't think they were in them days cared - about understanding. When they got a big family it was left 
to the woman to have all the troubles. They walked out of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They played no part in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not at all. No. Never saw a man pushing a pram in them days you know. You didn't
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you had a birthday was it ever any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. The only difference in a birthday was - me mother never hit you that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was the only difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The only day. It isn't very often you didn't escape a - a rap. You kno
w, either one way or another. Yes. But on a birthday, no. I think that was the only thing she could give us. You know. I sometimes feel sorry you know really. When she died - when she died, I felt a kind of a relief. But of course as I grew older -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 For you or for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
For myself. And as I - because I was seventeen and she wouldn't allow - I'd got to go work you know, same as I told you, off to bed. Not allowed to go out anywhere. The first - time I ever went out was for me seventeenth birthday. N
ow you can just listen to this - to see whether I had any privileges. And she said - now them days a pound note was a lot of money. And a pound note had just come out, replacing the sovereigns. And I - was working lace treading at - Poole's. Apprentice li
k
e. But before - previous to that I was mould running and that. The rough jobs. The low paid. But, of course - I went - an apprentice to - lace treading. Which was more money, ten bob, twelve bob. And I'd only been at it a month when I read about a hand la
t
he treader wanted. Well I've always been that way. If there's any money to be had and it's harder work I'll have it. So - I was taking a chance because the stuff was very - awkward to work for, it was - big bowls instead of small cups. But I took it. And 
I got a pound note. I was piece work. And it was a vast lot of money them days. But I only had a penny pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Out of the pound?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Had a penny. But anyway, she said for me seventeenth birthday, I'll take you to - the pictures. It was 
only a penny on the ticket, and we used to call it the Pall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
. It was then end of Eversleigh Road, the Alexandra. Well most likely you've heard your parents talk about it have you? And - previous to that like - as I've been walking home, 'cos I was pretty a
ttractive. I knew, but I never - never go out on it, because there was no aim for me in it. And - I hadn't got no boys on me mind you know. Still they - when I used to come up the opening like the boys used to whistle me. And I was petrified in case me mo
t
her was somewhere around, you know. But anyway, this - night - this - September. 29th when me birthday was, and she took me. And - I was amazed. With the - the amount of people that was in. And while we were waiting like for the - film to start - it was a
l
l lit up you know and - pianist was playing the piano. Wasn't orchestra or nothing. And one of the boys whistled. Whistled to me you know, turned me head like that, I knew who it was. I could tell whistle. Some of the boys from where I lived. And the next
 thing I remember - I was - coming to in that little house at the side of the - picture place. She'd hit me - as I turned back again. And it hit me on the temple and knocked me out. 'Cos I turned you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did anyone complain to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not that I know of, because I - I was knocked out. You see, and they carried me out - into room of this little house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she say anything afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, she said, I'll learn you to talk - to - to look at boys when they - whistle. Oh yes. Yes. But
 anyway - that was September, she died the following May. And I was getting to that age wanted to go - go out. Well any of the other - any other girls you know doing same, we went to the pictures and we've been - Stoke Hippodrome. And I used to think to m
yself, oh fancy, I can't get that far. Mind you Stoke, it seemed miles and miles away to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you remember anything special that happened Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Very often. Used to have a - a Christmas dinner but there was always fighting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Fighting between who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Mother and dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well - if they get the - got their drink. Well - perhaps it didn't happen every Christmas, but I know it had happened. Always - we never had a Santa Clause.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You had no presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, 
that was one thing that stuck in my mind - I was - seven - six or eight at the time I'm trying to tell you about. I told you about us going in these different Houses all round and about you know. And - at Christmas though I could see the children playing 
r
ound in the - the front street, 'cos they could play in the streets them days you know, with a ball and - bat and ball and - skipping ropes. And I remember as vivid - I've always thought about it - looking at all the children and thought it was funny he d
idn't come - our chimney. Yet he'd been all the others. And I was quite a big girl. Never had no Santa Claus.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How old were you before you remember getting presents at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We didn't have a present. I do remember we had some oranges and app
les. And a bag of sweets. Had no presents. Of course when you got four or five them days was a lot. I know when my children were little, used to take me all me time get - a Woolworth's present - for them you know, sixpence. That's what I say, kids today t
hey're ruined. Doesn't make 'em a better citizen. You must learn to want - before they can realize what things are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Before you can learn the value of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's it. To me it's all wrong. My children well must have spent pounds - pounds and po
unds for them. Well I'd - I'd gladly buy a child a nice toy. But I don't think I'd keep buying toys and toys and toys, all the year round, and then buying massive big toy at Christmas. Because they don't value 'em. I've been amongst it and seen it. They d
idn't get no more thrill out of that than I got out of an apple and orange. Because we never had one all the year through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So that to get it at Christmas was really a treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It was. It was. No, I don't believe in it. I like to see children have t
hings and I wouldn't deny them. But I do think - it's too far fetched these days. I think that's the trouble with the - they're - the world today. Children have got too many opportunities in too short a time of life. And they don't value the rest of their
 life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It's too much all at once in your opinion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
They won't - they won't accept anything. They won't come to accept the things as we did. If it comes back to what it was - it's possibility there, and it can you know. I mean, the unemployment tha
t's coming on now. And it doesn't - same as these - all these here factories when they're closing down that - the means test'll be that high. It'll have to come down soon won't it. So what'll happen to them children that haven't - that at - eight and nine
 
smoking cigarettes. Where do they get the money from. I think it's all wrong I do you know. I think the world's wrong. And it - and it starts at your own table. I said - well I won't say all of it. Because more or less one person - in that household'll go
 
wrong. Some families can have just the odd one and the other - the rest all right. But I do think the parents - it starts over their own table. Delinquency. And I - I wouldn't blame my mother if she frightened me forever - if I did things I see some of 'e
m doing now. And I'd do it to my children. I definitely would. I would. My children will respect me as highly as anything. Not only love - they respect me. Respect me, yes. They do. No, I don't believe in spoiling children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember having any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did anybody ever sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, only when they used to have booze ups and - used to ask me sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When they used to fetch you downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents ever play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no, they didn't. Oh no, they didn't not in them days duck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, no. No, you wouldn't get 'em in them days. I've never known }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 
\lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 em. Never. Never known 'em. Not of all the circles of people I've seen. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember your parents reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No I don't. I never saw a paper until I was - fifteen. In the house. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember a funeral in the family while you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well I remember a few funerals. Not particularly in the family. I do remember some of the neighbours you know. And - I was really glad of it myself because they used to let you go and have a biscuit and - a little drop of wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This was an occasion was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 An occasion, yes, we used - we used to go in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 especially}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  for it so we could have a - a long funeral biscuit. No, we had no deaths, only the little boy. 
Not before me mother died, of course the girl died after. That was - well I was grown up then. Oh yes, I was eighteen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you remember your parents going to funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. They didn't have any clothes. No. No, no. Couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You just went into the houses because you'd have a biscuit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In all the neighbours, yes, we kids did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you remember being taken out visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Friends, relations or neighbours or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no. No. Well me mother never got no clothes. Never - never had a coat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not even in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Well they didn't go anywhere did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So they stayed in all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh women did then more or less. Nearly all of them did. All as they did was have children, they got no
 clothes. And I tell you, me mother never had a pair of boots. Not like women's. Only old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We weren't my word. Kids did the errands, it was only - just down the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No major shopping trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh good heavens no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember going out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh never. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember any outings of any sort, Bank Holidays or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well - we had one from school
, we went to - Cresswell. And - that was the first time I had ever gone out. On a train. Didn't know what it was like. And - they were playing cricket you know after we'd had the tea party in the field, Cresswell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This was a school treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. A
nd - I was running I was. Well we were - in a game running you know. Racing. And as I was run - taking my turn to run, somebody - hit the ball, a cricket ball, and hit me right on the temple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you were knocked out again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So what happened on that occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh well I had to go to the hospital. And - 'course when I got home again I had another good hiding off me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She said I was running in the wrong direction. Should look to see where I was going. Putting everybody to the trouble. No, we daren't -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You daren't step out of line at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember going away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, good heavens no. Oh no. No, people never thought about holidays them days you know. Never heard
 of them. I'd never heard of Blackpool. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me something of how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Saturdays? As a child? Well the same as every - any other day when we were on a holiday. We wouldn't get up 'til late. And then we'd 
be playing. Playing in the yard.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just playing out doing nothing in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Always church. Always the church on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Only just the once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In the morning. Mass. Holy Communion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. Used to have a pinafore. We used to save that for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And that went over the top of your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That went over the top see. Oh yes, always saved that to go church in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You'd wear your ordinary everyday clothes underneath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh we - we'd only got one for wear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. It was very ordinary day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents ever go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Once a year me - me mother. Made her Holy Communion. With being a Catholic. Me father didn't bother, but me mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you brought up as a Catholic?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you went to Mass and Holy Communion on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes. Well you had to go as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But your mother didn't go every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, mother didn't go, no. Well she hadn't got - nothing to go in really but - she'd manage borrow - a coat or a cape off me aunties - 
always made Holy Communion once a year to keep - to keep in the faith. To keep in the faith, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But your father never went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No he didn't. No. He was a Catholica but he didn't go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 Catechism}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were there any church outings, Sunday school outings or anything of the sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no. I think there was for those that went - in the afternoon Catechisms. But we weren't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 allowed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I've no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She just wouldn't let you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, she just said, you go to church and - make your Holy Communion and that's enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever take part in any social activities organized by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. I was chose once - because I'd got a - a fairly decent voice - to go - on the stage, for St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 Patrick\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  Day at Broughton Town Hall. We were rehearsed and everything at school. But I couldn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She wouldn't let you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, but I hadn't got no clothes. See, you'd got to have a - a white frock. And I hadn't - got one. So I didn't go. I had to let 'em down.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was there any bother about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well the - the teachers - they - called and saw my mother. And asked her why she wouldn't let me go. She said, because she's got no clothes. Said, if you'd ha
ve told us we'd have borrowed 'em for her. She said, she was a leading singer. It was a French piece you know. Didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember the church running a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you belong to any other club organized by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you took part in one of the activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In nothing, I had no activities whatever. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Every night. Without fail. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just you children, or did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
We used to kneel side of the bed. Then in - wintertime we used to say our prayers in bed. We used to jump in bed because it was cold. We'd say them in bed. But that's grown with us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You've always done it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Always. I couldn't go to sleep without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You still say your prayers now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 If I was - dead tired, and - I just switch the light off and go straight off asleep I waken up ag
ain and say me prayers. It's in - something been born in me. Yes, bred in. Doesn't make me any better.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But you feel better if you do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well you - you - you feel as though you should do it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember your father taking an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh dear no. Never. No. I never heard it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you don't know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or why he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, no. No. The only views they got to my way of thinking now - well - since I've grow
n up - all as they wanted was enough - enough money as they could get a drink. And then - and then I think the rest of their pleasure was getting kids. And it wasn't my father, it was everybody else's more or less. In the lower classes. That was the only 
p
leasure they had I think them days. Getting - he was no man for dogs. Nothing of that. Some men used to have dogs you know, racing dogs, but - not him - my father. But, more or less I think nearly all men did. Some'd go work of course. It was drink and th
en come in - and bed. That was it. That's where the big families came in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember them voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No I don't, but I do remember - I was about eight when - we used to sing, vote, vote, vote. Them days. But I do
n't know - we didn't realize what it was for. You know some had red ribbon on, some had blue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But you didn't know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. We never heard it discussed at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you never ever remember your father voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. I think they voted but 
- we weren't interested, we didn't know what they were voting for or what it was. He used to go vote. But what for I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You said that your father didn't work very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But when did work what did he do with his spare time, what would he do when he came home from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well he'd sit in - in the chair, smoking his pipe. Never saw him doing nothing about the house. Well - there was never no - was never no attitude for improvements. There was nothing else to do, only just sit and smoke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was all he did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember your mother having any outside interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nothing outside the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, only just standing at the door talking to neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she ever go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. She didn't do her own shopping. Didn't go out shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You said most of the children did the errands that needed doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well they did. There was no big - stores or nothing of that then in - in streets. You'd ha
ve to go to Longton - and they weren't big shops really. But - anybody like - my parents, they never - never went out together. Nothing like that, it was just - Alice you go and fetch this and - there was no groceries bought in at the weekend like we brin
g.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No weekly shopping in other words?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No. Just hand to mouth. Quarter of this and quarter of the other. Yes. It was a poor life - for children. It was a poor life for them for that matter. Yes. Shouldn't have had the kids, she should have had les
s children and gone work. And helped out. That's all I can think of. I've always had to go work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your father go out any evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just over - not in the week. Weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no, not in the week. It was always weekends. And you could gamble if he got any money at all there'd be a fight.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well because me mother'd be jealous at - 'cos she couldn't get out I reckon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where would your father go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just in a pub. Close to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you say he went out to a pub would this be during the time that he was working regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or would this be even when he wasn't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, he - no, not when he wasn't working he couldn't. But if he did a little bit of work, we'll say he did three 
days. You couldn't bank on six days them days. But if he did three days - he'd earnt his pocket money for weekend. And that's what used to cause the fights. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So even though you weren't eating he'd still want his drinking money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh - oh he wouldn't give it up would he. Kept his pocket money out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Even though you weren't eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This is what the fights were over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It is, yes. Just that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever actually see them fighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh by God I did duck. Oh. Used to fight - they used to fight }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 vicious}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
. Oh she was strong. Wasn't a very big woman but - she was strong. He never could beat her you know. Only by kicking. He never could - down her with his first. But oh I come - run downstairs, we were in bed
 see, we used to run downstairs. And I saw 'em one night, both of 'em, they - they were in their night attire on the table fighting like - lions. Horrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 All because he'd been drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. It's all jealousy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she want the money so that she could buy food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well I suppose she'd want more money wouldn't she, then again - she wasn't able go through the door. I mean, when you're doing that all your life - I mean, you're pregnant twelve months out of two years all though your life - 
it makes 'em that way doesn't it. 'Cos they're not getting nothing out of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember your mother going to a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No. No. Not - not until the war was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She went then did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was just when she started - s
pend - buying clothes you know. 'Cos I was working. And Louie was doing - some work. And got me father's - grant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was your father in the Army then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And things began to get a bit easier then did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right, yes. Then she d
ied. It was - it was all through from '14 to '18, but she died in '17. Didn't have much pleasure. No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How old was she when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Forty-three. Had no pleasure. I think myself what a wicked shame. You know, to have kids like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember your father taking part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, he was never a sport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did he go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Good heavens no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did he ever bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember your parents belonging to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, well they hadn't got nothing to save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not funeral clubs, boot clubs or sick clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No. Only - what was it - insurance, and that was only - when the war was on. Never none before. It was only when - the war broke out. Me mother
 insured - insured herself. She - and she weren't that long, she didn't get anything. She had to be buried without any money. She wasn't insured long enough. She had her premiums. We had her premiums back. No. I think if she could have - had a better chan
ce you know - handling more money, she'd have been a much better woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It was poverty that made her the way she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It was, yes. She was a very proud person - you know. And I think it used to - get her down. Which is natural. I mean the surroun
dings was enough them days wasn't it. No furniture. Nothing of that. No nice curtains. Horrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well we never had any disputes - worthwhile. Never had any disputes. We've had quite a few since. Since we've grown up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But not while you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, we daren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was there any one that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, not really. No, I thought a lot about all of them, then I was left with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When mother died. Me father was away, he was in France. So I was left with 'em so - I sort of - mothered 'em - then, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was life easier then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Oh it was. But I - you see, then again - I never went anywhere until me mother d
ied. And then I was stuck with four children. After.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you didn't have it too easy either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Any of the kids in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Neighbours children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you play with your sisters and brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Me sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In street. Hopscotch or skipping rope you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you allowed to get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, me mother - if we did get dirty me mother used to - rap us. You know. We weren't neglecte
d in that line. Oh she was con - oh conspiculously clean with your hair. I used to dread - oh I used to - used to have wait in turn to have our heads looked, 'cos they didn't buy - didn't buy a teeth comb. We all had long hair - hair you know, big heads o
f
 hair, and four girls wanted some looking after. And - we always used to have to line up for have our heads looked. Every night. Every night, a few minutes you know. Then put in two plaits. Always had clean hair. I think if she'd had the chance she'd have
 been a real god wife. Good housewife and a good mother. I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents ever discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember belonging to any youth organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you do with your free time when you were a child, did you have any hobbies of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No hobbies, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, she wouldn't allow that. No pets. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about collecting things, did you ever collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about fishing or walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You never went walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. The farthest we went was the park and we lived right against it. Used to go up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you do up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Play. Just play about. But - if it was going to be wet or anything, mother'd say, you're not to go up the park. So that was it, we didn't.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So that was the only place you ever walked to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You didn't walk any distance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, it's only just - four streets - away. We were on Villiers Street, that's where we lived see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Never heard of them. Never heard of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember going to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So your first outing was on your seventeenth birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 On my seventeenth birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was the first time you'd been to anything of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. That's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You said when you started lathe treading and you got a pound you had a penny pocket money, did you
 ever have any pocket money prior to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh no. Me father used to send us a penny stamp each from France. A penny stamp that my mother used to use and send letters back again you now. And - I know when - before she died - she said, I wanted to save
 - ninepence for a brooch for me. I'd seen a nice brooch, mother of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 pearl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 with mother across it. So - I saved that penny for nine weeks and bought her that brooch and she only wore it once. She died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So your father wasn't at home when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was he allowed to come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Afterwards. He was sent home on - compassionate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you never had any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Before you started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember anyone outside the home helping your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never. No, well really and truly - me mother's people, they were a pretty proud lot. And - they just wouldn't bother with her. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 'Cos they thought she was as bad as me father, see, so they didn't - didn't bother with her. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Mind 
you nearly everybody was poor them days. But we were a little bit lower than most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What happened if your mother was ill or confined to bed, how did you manage then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I used to have to look after her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about when you were young though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I don't know how they went on then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you were a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16536882\charrsid10098272 younger}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Seven and eight. Well - we used to sleep together. Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about when she was having babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well we had - if she had 'em in the night we were brought - used to have a parlour - bed in the parlour when she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You were still sharing the bed with your parents then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes, we were. Until - she had - let's see, there was only one boy - that boy. We were all sleeping in bed - same 
bed until we had - Nellie and the boy. That was three of us in bed always with mother and father until she had another bed. Don't know where she had it from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So at one time there was five of you in a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Always. Yes. Always. Baby at the top and me and - Louie at the bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The baby at the top with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So how did you manage when she was having babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I don't know because - we never realized she was having 'em. And - I never thought about them. They may 
have brought us - out into the - kitchen, if it was in the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But you can't remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I never saw nothing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, but they didn't - mix.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They never saw each other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Never mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No - only neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So they never invited friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh they - good heavens they didn't. Oh no. No. Life was very primitive then. It isn't like now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about neighbours, did neighbours ever casually call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Neighbours were good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Would they call in without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. They would - pop in, yes. And - they would when - she was - you know, in labour I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents ever visit their neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No, mother wasn't much of a visitor. I aren't. I'm not much of a - I don't like visiting me own kids. I like going. But I - I'm always glad when I'm coming - back again. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When neighbours did come in would they ever be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh they wouldn't my word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you never remember any occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Had no - nice - does like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 No parties or get- togethers of any sort?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. 
No. No, no. All as I remember is when the war was on and me mother (ILLEIGBLE) the Bridge Inn with the other women you know, soldiers wives.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Prior to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nothing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 People divide society into di
fferent social classes and groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some belonging to another?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. Nothing like that ever occurred. That never struck my mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It never occurred to you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 People were never any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They just weren't any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No. No. I - I never have been that way. Really. I always - I never lowered me own dignity, never thought I was any lower than anybody else you know. No, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So at that time did you think that all people lived the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, I - I knew some of - lived better than others. But it didn't bother me. It didn't bother me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you give me any idea as to what sort of people you think lived better than others
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well, I always used to - reflect on me own relations. They went to work-and they had more than we ever had. And that's what always made me think. That's all what made me think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me which class or group you think you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Me? I don't know. You see - well mother's - now then - my mother's father - came from a - a wealthy family, in Ireland. And - me grandmother - that was his wife, was a maid - for them. And they got in - fell in love wit
h one another and that's why they came England. He was banished. They cut him off see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because he'd married a maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because he'd run out with her, got married here. But - I think the tradition is that all me mother's people are very proud. And 
- and I am. I - I've - of all my sisters I've got now, I am the proudest of them. I take after my mother for that. And all me mother's sisters are. Very - proud, you know. So - it's a throw back from me grandfather's people. They were - pretty well off pe
o
ple. They were Lester farmers the same as President Kennedy's father was. He came from County Cork as well you know. He was a master farmer. Yes. Yes. But - and I think that's where it is. I think that's where the pride is as I keep going work-. I'd rathe
r work for me own you know. And - have - Social Security.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me what sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What sort of people? Well I should think really good down to earth people. Myself. People that never had a chanc
e. Real good people. I never knew anybody from whereabout I lived, neither down - Heathcote Road or - up Dresden - that there was anybody I didn't like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were they all in similar circumstances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 All of them. They all were. They all were. We were in the quarter where it was poor. But none the less happier. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you were happy although you were poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Well we didn't know anything else did we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You consider that a lot of people in your area were in exactly the same position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
They were - they were all in the same position. Yes, they were all in the same position, the only difference that I didn't like about that type of class was - me mother and father fighting. 'Cos it used to terrify me. Other than that I accepted ev
erything. Good hidings off your mother, yes. Didn't bother me. It did bother me, I was worried about it, but I - I sort of accepted it. But I - I didn't like see 'em fighting. Didn't like to see that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Upsetting to a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh no. No. No. No, you're brought up to treat everybody - alike. Alike. And always treat people with respect. If they ask you - mother used to say, now if anyone as
ks you to go an errand you're to go. And if they want to pay you for it you're not to have it. Now to pay for it in them days was a piece of jam. We had to have it. You see, that's where the independence came in. Well very often if they asked me to go an 
errand I - I would have died for a piece of jam. But when they said, will you have a piece of jam Alice?, I said, no thank you, it's all right. I've been ready snatch it often.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But you hadn't dared because you're mother said you hadn't to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Of course I've not, you hadn't got to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember being told to curtsey or to show respect in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. We were brought up in that way. Not - no curtseying. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nobody at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember anyone showing respect to your parents like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No I don't think so. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In the district where you lived who was considered to be the most important person or who were considered to be the most important people?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well those days it was the priest. They never went no further than that. The priest was our first - port of call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And he was always considered the most important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Person, yes. Well - if there was a
ny bothers - we used to - mother used to send us along to the - church. Tell Father - Curan - Father Strogger, mother wants to see him, and ask - she used to - ask him - ask dad to sign the pledge. See, there was no summonsing and - no divorces, nothing o
f that. It was just the priest to make peace. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This signing the pledge business was to stop drinking was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's it. And - and - the drink caused unhappiness. Which it did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why do you think he was considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well because he was the only person should make your father go - off the beer for a couple of weeks - see. That's all I think anyhow.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Your father was frightened of him was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I think they respected 'em of course. You know, they respected th
e priest then. Them days. Well I think they do now, don't they. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were they scared of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, but not - not so much scared as respected 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What sort of people were the shopkeepers in the area and what sort of people did they associate with, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. I never knew who associated with anybody. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about your schoolteachers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They didn't. They didn't. They didn't associate very much at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you know what sort of people they would associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well I - I use to think that the teachers always went for the - the girls that were the better dressed. What we would call the middle class - them days, but they wouldn't be no different as I am today now. You know what I mean, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 money wise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why would you call them the middle class then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well they were better dressed weren't they, their parents went to work. We were looked upon as the poorest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you considered you were the poor class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We were the lowest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And the middle class was people whose parents went to work regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about your father's employer, when he was working, what sort of people would he associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well - I never had any contact there. No. Them days you know - your boss was your boss and that was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You didn't know anything about him otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nothing. No, no. Not until we were working - about 1920 you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Can you tell me what sort of people would you say went to church and what sort of people went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well I don't know, I - we've always been church people but - more or less everybody went - everybody's kids went church them days. Either Protestant or - Catholics. Yes. That's one thing that the parents did. Let 'em go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Insist that they went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Yes. But we weren't allowed go in Protestant churches - nothing of that. It was the Catholics you know. Very strict them days. Mind you, me I'm not - I'm not a religious person. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was it forced upon you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well it - it is in your school isn't it. Catholic schools it was - was them days. It isn't now you know. Oh no, not now. No. It was very bad then. And I know when we were - when I was quite young - they used to have m
agic lanterns. Well it was at a Protestant school at - at nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You weren't allowed to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
We weren't allowed to go. But I think it was all wrong. I used to do even then. I - I don't - I don't believe in anything like that. I don't, I always t
hink there's a - there's only one God and everybody worships the same person to go to. I - I think it's pack of daft. I do, I - I do really, I - either for - Protestant or Methodist or Catholic - whatever it is, there shouldn't be any animosity through it
.
 There's only one God isn't there. And - and if you're going to - if you're going to adore that one person you're no - you're not better than that other person. If he was a - if he was a - an African. He believes in his God. It's his way of thinking isn't
 it, so why should why should he be stopped. I think all this Irish effort is all that. It's all wrong you know, don't you think on? I don't believe in it. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Where you lived did all the people in the poorer classes as you were yourselves have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or was there any varying?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No, there was no variations duck. No. We were all the same. Some - some of them were - that's where me mother used to think she was prouder than them. They were more scruffier. 
And they used to swear more. And they didn't bring their children up right. You know what I mean, they weren't particular what they said to the children or wheat the kids say back. Well that - none of that happened at our house. We were very poor but prou
d. And strict. It's the best thing as ever come out. Being strict is. I'm a fanatic. It's made me a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 damn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 sight worse since I see what happens in the world today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This bothers you does it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I think it does, I worry - wondering about where - how my 
grandchildren are coming on. And yet all my grandchildren have been brought up exactly how I brought them. That's funny isn't it? Yes, but these - kept strict you know. Kept on the - and there isn't one of them that talk - what shall I say - common. They 
don't, none of them. Not one of them, they don't. I'll say that for me other sisters as well. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They've all been pretty strict in their families have they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 In - they - brought them up - as near as they could, you know, properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Them days? No. No, there were none of that them days. Not where I lived there wasn't. No, there wasn't where your father lived, none of that. There was nothing like that, not now, the - the - it's all
 groups now, well they weren't then. The only group I ever remember was the - suffragettes. And they weren't round here. No. No, everybody was - free and easy. All as people wanted them days was some work. And they would have worked. How they spent it was
 their business wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You think most people were pretty much the same in the ways they lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. They were, yes. They only wanted a chance. 'Course later - later in life they all - picked up when the war broke out you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And things got better then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Got better, and they all fall back again and all. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh I'll tell you this truth - my mother used to think they were rough. She - she was a little bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 bigoted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Who did she think was rough?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
It was the parents and they used to let the children talk. And it used to emphasis because my mother wouldn't. She wouldn't stand none of it, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So she considered those people - rough did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She - she considered them, they were - illiterate. To a certain degree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When were people considered particularly respectable then if she considered people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well my mother always thought the same as I do. They were respectable if the
y knowed their manners. It didn't mean - money. It meant the way they lived. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you ever remember there being a distinction of this kind, the rough and respectable distinction, between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Oh yes. That was - pointed out that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did that come to show itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well in - and I've heard me mother and father talking like - the wages, you know, brick layers labouring, and - I've heard - he used to say, such a body is a joiner, he gets twice as mu
ch money. See? That's the only thing I remembered. And then - when he worked in a pit he used to say, oh such a body works on face, he's likely be able go out and dress up. Got more money see. Money was the trouble - there. There wasn't enough of it. In o
n
e direction and - and I think their community was another. I don't think the men them days'd - would - bring theirselves in to be - domesticated. As they do now. No. They - they just got that way of thinking that - all that the woman was for was bed. And 
t
hey went out and they got their wages. Not only my father but the others as well. 'Cos - they couldn't have got drunk without money. And if they didn't have much money, so it wasn't going at home was it. That's how the kids used to be barefoot. Because th
ey spent - they had their pocket money first, see? And that was it. Their way to live - mind you, girls today wouldn't stand that and I don't blame 'em. They wouldn't have it would they? But what's more, they no need have children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Women today are so much more independent aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
That's it, they're independent and what's more they - they don't have big families. You can live easier not having big families can't you. Can. 'Course it is, if you - two wages is better than one, but if you're havi
ng kids you can't - go work like that. I went. I had - five to live. But I always went to work but your children were neglected. It was just that - mind you, I wouldn't have had above one. But I just didn't know how not to have 'em. You weren't - you know
, we weren't up in that - line. No, I mean, you went to bed to enjoy yourself and that was it. You'd got no other option had you. Really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So this is ignorance again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It is ignorance, yes. Even in my time it was all ignorance. Because I was a per
son as wanted to get on. I didn't mind how much I worked. I wanted to get on, I will if I - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 'cos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 I'd got a big family I couldn't. And - and that's what it had - it did materialize. I was having babies and I couldn't. The only difference was I didn't know h
ow not to have 'em. If I got my time over again I wouldn't have 'em, I'd have two, don't say I'd have one. But I'd wait for about five or six years. And then - finish. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember your parents having the same attitude to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes, they were pretty near the same. The only groups were the neighbours. Well everybody was more or less the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And your parent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 s attitude towards them was the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just the same, yes. Oh aye. Oh - better neighbours then than there's ever been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Your neighbours then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Neighbours? They were. They weren't - them days they weren't - they didn't walk in your house and have a look round, say, oh she's got this. That never occurred. Never occurred that didn't. They just wa
lked in one another's houses and - they never looked for anything because there's nothing to look for. They're all in the same standard. And - it stopped a lot of jealousy. In that way you know. They were all equal. And that was it, you couldn't do nothin
g
 about it. But I - I still think it was a happier life. We've been talking about the same thing today at work. If you could just look back - it was much happier if you could have got more money. A little bit more money - for food, and clothes. Only just a
 little. Just to live nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You think the times themselves were happier do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
By gum I do. Definitely. Oh yes. People at my times, they used to sit on the front - you know, on the front steps, talking to one another. And - quite happy. No arguments, no nothing. Now they'd walk past you. Oh no, they were more together then. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 More}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  togetherness them days. Never be the same again that won't. Won't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But this is what you get with supposed affluence isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It is, yes. But - at Christmastim
e - your neighbours'd come and sing carols at your door. They wouldn't now. Now would they? They wouldn't. Oh, I'm not on about a couple, I'm on about four or five. Quite a lot of 'em all get together, an sing carols. No, I don't suppose - like the same a
s
 I am now. Won't mix. It was just as everybody was on - more or less on equal terms. And if there was anybody who got a little of bit of something they were out. You can find it wherever you go. But there was too many of the - one type - to notice the oth
ers much, see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes, well - not - class of people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 
No, because wherever I went - well, more or less everybody - everybody was in the same boat. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But you just got the odd occasion
al one. A little bit better off. And - and it was always losing their families. It wasn't done with 'em. It was those who left them. Because the wife could go out to work }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 then}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 . So instead of bringing one pound in it was two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 More could be done with two than with one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Yes. And then of course they thought they were a little bit above you. So - they move out. That's it. They go in a better street, see, thinking they're bettering themselves, which you couldn't blame them - really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I remember me uncle. He was an insurance - man. Inspector. Used to think he was a gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well because he used to dress so nice. Got a good position with a 
book and pen. See, well - he hadn't. My mother's brother. Not my father's people. They were - very poor people. But me mother's people were proud, same as I told you. It went back. It went in all of them, they were all proud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, only just those two as come for me auntie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You never remember seeing any others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. All the fights as they ever had - they never used to bother about the police, we used to tell the priest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you never remember seeing police in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well walking round. But - not many you know them days. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you think of him, when you were naughty did your mother ever threaten to call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, there was no threats. You had a bump.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How do you suppose he treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well, we never saw 'em. Hardly ever duck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just in the streets occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh very, very rare. Very rare. Wasn't many police then. We'd be
 frightened to walk past 'em. 'Cos we knew he was somebody superior you know. Weren't the same as now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You didn't have much dealing with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. When we paid any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever see anything of your landlords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, on the Mondays. We'd see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was the day you made sure you hadn't got a fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They were watching and he - he couldn't see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But at times when they could afford to pay the rent did you see your landlord then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
It's funny you should say that, now when we went - from Dresden and Florence, we went down to Hathbridge Road. For the second time. I was thirteen then. Well we'd be about - nearly thirteen. And - I remember Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 Stoddard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  came for the rent
 - and when he knocked at the door me mother went, she says, the rent man's here. You know. Just like that. And he said, rent? He says, we wouldn't have had to have gone out of the other house if we'd have paid rent. Could you imagine anything like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's what she said to him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Me father said it to the - to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 rent man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 As good as telling }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15954510\charrsid10098272 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  you weren't going to pay it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. He said, we wouldn't have had to shift out me other house if we'd have paid the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Don't know I'm sure. But very shortly after that - war broke out. So the rent was paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 By?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, by me mother. Out of her allowance. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Obviously it was a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh good Lord it was. I've had a struggle but I wouldn't like one like that. I wouldn't - I wouldn't bring children in the world for that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you think about it at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When I was little? I didn't know anything any different. But - when I was seventeen 
and I - after me mother died - I thought - I tried to make things different for the - kids. I tried it all roads you know, started decorating the house and that. Wallpaper you know. Buying little pieces of secondhand furniture. But I wouldn't have liked t
h
at life. I wouldn't. No, I don't think myself - I've had a terrible life myself but - we always had plenty food and a good fire. You know, the kids, their shoes have - been very old and had to be mended when they were all little. Because we didn't have mu
ch money them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But you weren't as poor as when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
By God we weren't. No. Oh no. Well as I say we would have been if I - if I hadn't have gone to work. But there wasn't as much work them days for women as there was when I was a woman. Wasn't the same. In any case women didn't go out work much then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because they were so busy having babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, and they'd got nothing to go work in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When - me mother was living? No. No. So - it must be that if you didn't go work you couldn't get none, 'cos we never had nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever apply for any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I don't ever remember them. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never applying for help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Well I doubt wheth
er they'd get any because - they'd want to know why you weren't working or if you'd been different places. Well I don't suppose they dared go after anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because your father wouldn't work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's it. There was work in the pits even if you we
re only on short time, but - couldn't stick it. No. No. No, it isn't same as it is now you know. I was on the Guardians, I was. I was - on the Guardians. But it was because - it was because - it was genuine, me husband was ill, you know. He was T.B. So - 
that's a different thing altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When there was someone in the district of whom the people strongly disapproved was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, I never remembered anything duck. No. I haven't ever remembered anything like that. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You don't ever remember there being an effigy made or anyone being made to leave a house by rough music or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no. No, I haven't heard of anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did any of the neighbours intervene when your parents were fighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. 'Cos if they had have done me mother'd have put 'em out, wouldn't have let 'em interfered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were you ever given lessons at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, Good Heavens. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh well, 
when I first went school it was when me sister was my mother was in bed with me sister, and she was three years younger than me. So I'd be three.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you go to full day school or half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Full day, there wasn't half time then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What time did you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What time did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It would be nine o'clock, I don't remember it. Four. Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you go home at lunch time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It was only - just at the end of the street. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I was only a baby. And it was Florence Board School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I was only in a baby class, see. Boys and girls together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You say it was only across the road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just at the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So how long did it take you to get there from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well - one of the neighbours used to take me I think. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh a minute. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you went home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well I'll tell you truthful, I - didn't like it. No. I didn't like it because - I'm not going from back - then when we've just been talking - as I got older. Because me mother used to keep me at home from school so long and so often that - a
nd having no shoes - or - stopping at home truing - go pick a bit of coal or anything like that, that when I went to school - I couldn't catch up on the lessons, I used to have a lot of pain, which is no fault of me own. So I always - feared school. I - w
h
en I - if I go the cemetery now, and I pass that school I get that fear. Because I was always in the background - of not going to school. And I never go there early. 'Cos me mother never used to get up. And I used to be off and with the other two girls, a
nd that was it. You got later you got dragging 'em behind with you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You said you had to carry one of your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That was how she got no shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you think of the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I was afraid of them. Then. I was afraid of the
m. And - I was never a person that they ever bothered with because we were - so poor. Well then - you felt as if you were in the background all the time. And you couldn't catch up on your lessons, because you got - too much worries. I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 At home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I'd always got me mind on things at home, well I am like that now. I still worry - about home. I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important - manners for instance, tidiness, punctuality, ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, they 
didn't bother. The only thing - I remember that - they pulled me up for was - I - if I - if I'd have been a girl that had got - had the time I would like to have dressed nice, you know. I've always been one for nice clothes, and - when I started getting m
e
 own I started to - try get the nicest and look smart. And - me auntie gave me a bit of yellow gauze once and I put it on - as a big bow on me neck. When I went in the school of course teacher snatched it off me. Off me neck. And as she did it - scarred m
e neck a bit. And of course - and I was - having a wash, next - next - no, same night, having }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 a wash.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 Mother says, what's the scar? We always had to have a wash overnight. Always. Because it wasn't much trouble then next morning. What's that scar on your ne
ck? And I said - with it being rough gauze you know, she pulled it like that. So anyway - me mother went up the school. She said, what have you taken the - what did you take the scarf off my girl's neck for? She said, she didn't want a big scarf like that
 sticking out. She said, and it doesn't go - it isn't appropriate with her other clothing. So me mother walloped her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Hit her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Yes she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She said, when I put a bow on my child's neck - she didn't put it on 
- you leave it on. She says, unless she's dirty. If she's dirty you take it off her. Oh yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Was there any trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They sent the police to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The priest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The priest again, aye. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 And mother told her she says, look - I 
chastise my children and the teachers are allowed to do the same thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But she's not allowed to snatch things off a child's neck unless she asks. She was like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 She'd stand up for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Definite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What happened if you did something the teachers disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well you had cane didn't you. But you daren't go home and tell your mother. Had it again. Because you'd perhaps done something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were the girls punished the same as the boys, were the girls caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Which girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The girls in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. They were. Oh definite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 For what sort of offences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well if you were giggling, you know, and you - and if you didn't do your lessons right. And I could never do mine right could I. Well I wasn't there
. I was all there, I had - it was only - I was very good on everything bar arithmetic. And I was good on - just do the additional sums and the subtraction sums. But when it come to long divisions I hadn't got enough brain power. Used to get more numbers t
han I started with. So I had the cane. And I never could find out how it was. But I hadn't got enough coaching. I hadn't had enough instructions you know. Never at school. Never at school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did they never go to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no, they didn't, only when - that time - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were the other children in the school from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. They were, yes. Mostly. Nearly all of them. There was one or two that was - little bit better off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But generally speaking they were all mostly the same type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 They were all with the teachers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, I don't think so. I think they made more fuss of the - better dressed ones. No, no, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Were there any gangs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or any children that were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, I never saw it. No I never saw it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you go on to any other school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you stayed at the one school all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. All my life, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Thirteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, you couldn't - couldn't get away quick enough. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you attend any part time education after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes I do. I think - if I'd ha
ve - been brought up - with a good education, I could have - gone further. 'Cos I was - good at history and geography and everything. But it was just the long division of sums, I couldn't concentrate on them, and I think it was the background that did tha
t. And fear. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh yes, I should think so. Mind you I've learnt more since I left school than I learnt when I was there. I've learnt more since I've had television than anything. I have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well the first full time job I was handle making. And - you had to go
 piece work. And I earned - three shillings. I remember when I drawed the money on the Saturday, didn't work a week in hand them days, you were paid Saturdays. And I went and changed - changed this three shillings for all pennies. Make it look a lot.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I went myself from school. When I left school. On the Saturday. Friday - went on Saturday and got it. 'Cos worked Saturdays then you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just went to a factory and asked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Oh I went to about five factories, but I got one. But I didn't like it. I didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 From half past seven 'til six at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Saturday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. No, Saturday one o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We didn't. You didn't my God. We didn't. There was nothing of that them days duck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You were paid three shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you feel that this was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I thought it was a - an immense lot of money. Then. But whether me mother said anything about it, don't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But you felt it was a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I felt it was a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you give all this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What was it spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I don't know, me mother - bound it in with the other. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have any back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Penny. Penny. 'Course penny was a lot then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you do with your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I used to spend it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 On what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Ha'penny - on - Saturday and ha'penny Sunday. Sweets. You'd get four ounces a penny then you know. 
Used to have a ha'porth of sweets on Saturday and ha'porth Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Then you didn't have any the rest of the week until the following weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I've always got on well with 'em. Always. Always got on well, I do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Very good. I never had no - quarrels. Never. Anywhere. I've never been late. Never lost any time. And I've always been - you know what I mean - same as I am at home
. Well perhaps not this week I'm not doing nothing. But if there's a job to be done I do it. And I - and I don't feel as though I've done it unless I've done me best, see. I think that's why - they give me choice of jobs now. I can turn me hands now to tw
o or three different jobs at work. And they just come to me, say, Alice, will you do with for us? Say, yes. Say, well you've just got us out of another bit of trouble, see. And that's all the trouble I've ever had. I never grumble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you feel about your first employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well - well like - you never saw 'em did you. You never saw your employers, you always saw the managers. But I've got on all right with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Handle making? Well - I thought -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You say you were very keen on this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Handle making, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Why not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well I didn't think there was enough - a little bit artistic I am you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 There wasn't enough to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. It was a bit - mucky. You know. I'm not frighte
ned of dirtying me hands. But - there was no aim to it. I don't think I liked the people either. Really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did that job alter your attitude to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I never liked school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did going to work alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I'd rather go work than school. Oh yes, I would. Oh yes I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How long did you do this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I'd been there for about - six weeks, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Then I went - me - me auntie came. Who, as I told you, we thought w
as rich. Would I go - cutting paper for her. Paper cutting. And I went and - I worked with her. Until I was - sixteen. Then I went - work with a lather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you were print cutting did you do the same hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes, same hours. Only got three bob. I got three bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you still give it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you have any of that back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No, but she used to let me go - clean me aunties, Friday nights. I used to go straight from work, and - scrub all the floors for her. 'Cos it was all brick floors then. Used to give me threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you could keep that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No, mother used to let me have a penny out of that, see. That was tuppence. And do you know, when we used to go work - at dinner - at night times, everything was set out like - jam knife and little - trays and all that. They only had jam for their tea.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But it was all set out very nicely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh very nicely, yes. I didn't know - jam went on, I thought jam went on bread, I didn't know it went on - in a little -
 dish. And - and that was a treat, I used to wait for Friday nights. Have our jam out of a dish, I liked it. 'Cos they were always nice as well you know. I liked that, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you were print cutting how did you get on with the people you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Well - there again, me - me - it was me mother's sister. And they were a bit snobbish. And they didn't mix with anybody, there only another - couple in the - shop. They never mixed with 'em. So of course I - I didn't have to. I wasn't allowed to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Because you were with your mother's sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did your employer treat you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The manager's very nice. Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I liked 'em. I liked 'm very much. But - there - I heard them 
talking like about - I don't know how it come about, I heard me Uncle Herbert talking about some - somebody working in the clay that - they got more money than those - they worked and they were the best - best gold printers they were. And - it just struck
 
me on the idea you know - thought myself, oh dear. Can get more money in the clay. I can get another job I shall do. Of course I told me mother, I said - will it be all right if I go back after job in dinner hour? What do you want another job for? I said,
 
well if it's more money - she said, what - what's give you the idea? I said, well I've heard me Uncle Herbert talking about it. He said they get more money in - clay department than they do, and they had to work you know they did. And that is how I went. 
So, when I went they said - would you like to go scolloping? So I said, well I - I've never done it. I said, but I - I'll have a look what it's like. So - showed it me and I thought myself well it's - it's nice but you can't do much. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 It was a very,very whatsit job, highly skilled. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And - I said, I'll }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 accept}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 it but I can't - I won't be able do it very quick. Said, no, you mustn't try to. Of course when I went to work in the shop I saw these 'ere other women on these lathes. Mind it was terrible hard work. And 
- of course I got talking to the girls at dinner - in dinner hour, and - they said as they got - twelve bob a week. So I asked him, I said, if there comes a vacancy could I go work lathe treading? Twelve shillings a week. He said, oh you'll have to earn p
iecework. I said, oh I'll work hard. And that's how I went. Got this 'ere twelve bob. Well I'd only been on it a week or two when I went and got a head lathe, for a pound a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you have to do in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh what you had to do, you stood o
n one leg - and - you - it had a wheel attached to a plank - of wood. But you has to put your foot on this plank of wood, and it's got kind of a quid on it. And it went round, and it took this great big wheel round. Well this big wheel - with the rope on 
- it sent a little spindle round, where the man had got to work from, with a cup on it. See, a clay cup. And he used to shape it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 But it had got to go round very, very quick. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It was terrible hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So you just treated the lathe so to speak?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So I treaded the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 lathe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 , and I sponged the cups at the same time, you worked with your hands and your feet, yes. But - I stuck it because it was the best paid them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you were paid twelve shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Twelve bob. It was a lot of money that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And after how many weeks you became a head lather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And then I went and got - somebody said that - on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 Amieson's}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  they had lathe treader - was ill, so had to give it up. So I went up and asked him if I could have it. And I went. And I tell you I got this 'ere pound a week. It was a lot of money them days you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What sort of hours were you doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh from - half past seven 'til six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 With your Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And Saturday }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Still no holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh no. Oh there wasn't my word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you feel that pound was fair then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I thought it was - a terrific lot of money. Mind you I worked - I worked terribly hard for it. But work didn't come in it. It w
as what I achieved with it. That I wanted. This was - well it was a big income that was you know. It was. And it really put me mother on her feet. You know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you still continue to give all this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. I mean, I started having - clothes then, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did she give you more back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
No, she didn't give us much - she didn't give me more back, she gave me sixpence. But - she started going the market, see, and bring in sweets and biscuits - for the other kids as well
. It - it made such a difference in our house that money did 'Cos it was a vast lot of money a pound was. She never had that much off me father. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So it was quite an occasion to have it from you was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 It was. Same as I say, she was just enjoying life - she died while I was working there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So how much were you getting back at this time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Sixpence. Sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you were doing a lot with that sixpence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well it lasted all week. Last all week. Get four ounces a quarter of sweets then for a penny you know. Could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 So it was lasting a long, long time?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you get on with the people you worked with then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Fine. Always have. Always got on with 'em. If I couldn't get on with people I wouldn't mix with - I wouldn't stop with 'em. No, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 but}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  to - I'd got to - like 'em and mix with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about your employer there, how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Smashing. Smashing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I thought he was very good. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you like that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Lathe treading? Well I liked it because it was a lot of movement in it. But that was all right while I was single. But when I got having children, I didn't like it. But I'd got no other choice, I couldn't do anything else. 
So I had to stay. Stay put. It's been a terrible hard life. But they don't do it now you know. It's all done by machinery. No, it's done by machinery. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How long did you continue lathe treading then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Until I was - fifty-seven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You've done it 'til fairly recently then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I've done it until they - they closed 'em down. 'Til I was fifty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So what have you done then since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh Lathe treading all through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What have you done since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And then I went scalloping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You did a little bit of scalloping before you went lathe treading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Yes, but it's just the same now. Yes. But it isn't the same now - as it was then. You see, the china clay was flexible - then. You daren't handle it, it'd break
. Well learning on that it would worry - it'd worry me. In case I broke them. Because you weren't allowed to break 'em. Whereas now - the bodies more heavier. Stand more knocking about. I can do it now. But since I've been - sixty, I've been handle cuttin
g. Cutting handles. And - mind I used to have scalloping between, I've been scalloping today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What's scalloping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Making all the fancy tops on cups. Cutting it - the clay out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You have to do that by hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh yes. Yes. Oh that's all right - once you know how.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So that last few years you've been handle cutting and scalloping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Handle cutting. Cutting - and scalloping cups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Have you had to serve a training period or apprenticeship for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh yes. Oh yes, I - and then - when you were - go lathe treading, you didn't get the full amount - of money, you had to allow so much - out of it. For your training. Oh aye. 'til you're twenty-one. Then you got your full money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, Potters. Potters Union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 didn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 .

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You didn't go to any of its meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh well - no. Never. Just paid my dues. No, I never went. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well in our - in our line duckie - I don't think you'd go the world over and find people of a more - who were more easily satisfi
ed than the potters. They've had less strikes than anybody. I only ever remember one strike. And I have been working - fifty-nine years. Only one strike. And that was - when the depression was on, everybody was striking. Got no other choice then. But the 
-
 but of course now you've got a better chance. Now - I mean all the unions are together now aren't they, they're all more amalgamated and - livings different now. The cost of living rises, they hadn't used to do then see. When it does we've got to have - 
r
ises. Of course - these - other industries, they strike before you know where they are. They've got more money than - we ever get. And they strike quick. I think that wants knocking in the head you know. I do. I did, I think it's disgraceful for anybody a
sk for four pound a week rise. I do, I think it's - shocking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You think it's too much do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Oh I do. If you have four pound a week rise everything's got to go up according with it hasn't it. And that - other peoples a lot in that industry that live in that particular vicinity, they've got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 to suffer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 the same. Don't you think? Of course they have, if the food and everything goes up, the rates and rents. Because they've had a big rise. I don't think it ought - I think all rises ought to come throug
h Government, I do. There ought to be one big union. And I didn't believe in shop stewards at all. To me they're nothing, only a lot of big mouths. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 Somebody's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  like sold 'em out for. Never believed in 'em. I believed in having a leader. But not shop stewards and all that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 paraphernalia}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 . Wants }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 cutting out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 , that does.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 didn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  think it serves any useful purpose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No I don't, I think they're nothing, only agitators.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No. Not in our industry there wasn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 We're told that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes, but I wasn't in that line. I wasn't in that line. I was just in - the clay department. Where the tr
ained craftsmen would most likely be - the mould makers. And your - the other ones that - made the patterns. Pattern makers. They were craft - craft men. They were different than us. But there was never no strikes, not even with them. I never saw - I neve
r saw much partiality amongst 'em. They got more money. Well they got - they ought to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But no division of interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well - no. No. But I think they ought to have more money, their - their work }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  more important, I mean we had to carry on from them. We couldn't have had our cups made if they hadn't have - designed 'em. We couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No, I don't think so. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 
I mean, when you've been brought up in it, it doesn't. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. You only just live - how you've lived. As you grow older. When you've lived a lifetime you accept it don't you, I think you do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 After you left school you continued living at home, did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So life went on pretty much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Just the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you spend Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, just went church. Of course we did more cleaning, 
when we got older we had to clean - of a Sunday. Probably scrub upstairs, you know, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Never. No. Never entered me head. No. No, all I wanted was a good job, some wages and that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you not have any particular political views at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. And haven't now. I haven't now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But not before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No I didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No, I hadn't. No, you were asked and if you didn't that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You weren't a member of any party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You never had much spare time when you were younger at school did you and you didn't go out much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You played with the neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What did you do now that you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well when me mother was living we had to go bed just the same. I was still classed as a child. Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you never go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Not while your mother was living?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. No. Never. Well there was nowhere to go was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What about just for walks with your friends or girls you met at work and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No, me mother wouldn't allow me. 'Cos I had no - no girl friends up there, wouldn't have had nobody - come to your door 
or anything of that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You were seventeen when your mother died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So what happened after that then? Did you start going out in the evening then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well when me mother died - as I tell you I was looking after the - the children. Th
en - I used to go dancing. Used to call it Dirty Curtains down Felton. Used to go there dancing. But - it was just a nice night out but - to me, I wanted something a little bit better than that. It was scruffy. It wasn't my idea - I like something big, go
o
d, you know. I didn't - never got any farther than that. Never. Not until - I was married to Jim, and - I worked on - Radford's down Fenton. And with me being the only one that her husband was away like - they used - they all sort of took to me, all the w
omen did, and - it was - two couples they - I used to go with 'em to their house, and - the weekends, and then occasionally we would go Manchester, on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 ut}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
 ballroom and I thought it was lovely. There was an outdoor ballroom. And I won the - first pri
ze for dancing there. I thought it was gorgeous. It was all floodlit you know. It was lovely. I enjoyed anything like that. Couldn't go - often enough there. It was only one and eight return, you know. And - that's where I did most of me dancing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When you were younger, after your mother died, you started going out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. Dirty Curtains, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 A young - a girl named Alice Parks that worked on the factory, you know, me and her used to - dance together. Never bothe
red me about boys. Never occurred to me you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you make any new friends at that time, either boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. Only just this girl. Hilda Parkes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did you meet her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Well she worked at the same place see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And you used to meet each other of an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
And then - she used to go - with me. I used to go with these couples and - used to take her with us. And - because we used to dance together. Well they used to have a drink see, on the tables outside. And - that'
s how - we used to pass the time. Never went out in the week but we looked forward to Saturdays. Well I couldn't really because I'd got the kids. Well they weren't little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did you ever take friends home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. I've never - I never have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Even when your mother was dead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your father not allow it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 I never did. I didn't do it, I didn't take any friend home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How did life continue at home now your mum was dead with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Oh well, I only stuck it
 until I was - just before I was twenty. And me father was at home, he was courting this woman. And - started drinking and doing so - I've got a photograph of me mother over the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 whatsit}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 . In them days - yes, in them days when you did your washing I used t
o - I was pretty proud of me washing. And more particular and more proud of me ironing because I was a good ironer, and - I know I was - putting - putting these things over the line and this woman that - was going about with me father, she says - you're -
 
me father sat here and she sat here like. You're exactly like your mother. You know. She didn't like me. I could tell she didn't like me 'cos I didn't give her - no encouragement you know, I didn't like the idea of it. And - I said, well is there any - an
y
 fault you can find there, other then you've got her husband? Aren't you satisfied? And then me father said, don't you talk to her like that. I said, I am twenty. I said, and I'm allowed to speak in this house, now. It's as much mine as yours. 'Cos I was 
doing the working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You were bringing the money in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Yes, I was. Anyway - she says, if I was him I'd bang you up the bloody ear'ole. So I turned round and I banged her instead. And I could hit as well. Them days. And it knocked her straight up. She
 stood up see. So I hit her, it knocked her, and she fell and the chair broke under her. Of course I had to shift. I daren't stop there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your father get hold of you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 He didn't have chance, I shot. And - it'd be about - turned eleven o'clock
, half past eleven at night. And I run across the banks, which brought you into Endsell Road. And - I thought to myself, whatever am I going to do now, got nowhere to go. 'Cos a thing I'd never done before you know, never experienced it. And there was a y
o
ung woman there, and she was with a fellow. She said, Alice whatever are you doing out here? Well I told her. I said, well I've go nowhere to go. So she said I'll find you somewhere. So I said, where, I said, I haven't me got me coat nor nothing? Well she
 said, I'll take you across to Mary }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 Harding\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
, it was across the road you know. So - I didn't know this woman. Anyway I went in. She says, yes, come in. She says, I've only got the one bed. She says, you'll have to sleep with me and the two children. So I s
aid, oh I'll fix myself up somewhere - later on. But anyway I stayed there - about a month. And - we got another bed, and - she was at - her husband and her were parted. She had a baby while her husband was in the Forces you see and - they'd parted, you s
ee, so she was all alone. And - this Friday night she'd gone fetch her babies from nurse like and I thought myself - there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 mirror}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  like over her - grate, high, up. And I was cleaning this and singing. All of a sudden I just saw the reflection of somebo
dy in the doorway. He was a smart soldier. When I turned I said - who are you? And - he started laughing. I said, I'll ask you again, I said, who are you? He said, I'm Mary's brother. Oh, I said, you'd better come in then if you are. I said, by the way, I
 
said, what were you staring at? He said, I was looking at your legs. Looking at your legs, he says, and now I've seen your face, he says, it's nicer than ever. I said, you're a bit - forward aren't you. You know, I was - I was frightened of him really. An
yway I said, wait here a minute? I said, I'll go and fetch her - I couldn't get out quick enough. That's how I met me husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 He was this Mrs Harding's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And that's how I met him. Well - we - he came like - came in with - Mary came in wit
h the children, said, what are you doing here? Said, I'm off for four days. Said, why only four days? Said, oh I'm going to India. Said, oh, she said, that's a bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 sudden}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  isn't it? He said, yes. Well anyway, we sat talking. So, I said, to Mary I said, I'll
 get in your bed and let him lie in that other spare bed you know. So - he said, oh no need, he said, I'm not tired. I said, well I am, I've got to go work - Saturday you know. We sat up talking 'til two o'clock. He was telling me all his life, at first s
he was telling me all about his life, he'd got no home nor nothing, and - I told him how I come to be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Did your father ever make any attempt to get you back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 He never came after you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. No. So anyway - he said - oh, h
e said, I told you from the first that I liked you, well - soon as you turned your face round. Well I said, what does that imply? He said, well what would you say if I asked you to marry me?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 This was straight away, the same day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 The same night.
 Yes. But anyway, I said, I'm not that bad off you know. I said, I know I haven't got a home, I said, I've still got me pride, I said, I don't want to get married. He said, well I - I shan't be able to see you again he said, for seven years. He said, and 
-
 'cos he was going away for seven years see. He says, and I've got no home, he said, and - if I could put me trust in you, he said, could you - could you trust me? And I said, no, I don't want to be married, I said, I've just had enough of married life wi
th me sisters you know. So Mary says, well why -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Looking after your sisters you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
Yes. Mary said, well why don't you marry him? She said, I can - guarantee he's a good boy. She said, he isn't anybody's you know Alice. She said, no more than y
ou are. She says, you've neither of you got a home. Says, you can't call this home. Why don't you make it up and get married? So I said, well it's a big chance. I said, it isn't a love marriage, I said, it is a marriage of convenience, and I' - 1 take you
r sister's word, I said, I will. We were married three days later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Before he went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And we never went bed. Never went bed. We were married two o'clock and he took the Stoke train quarter to four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How long before you saw him again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And -
 I was writing to him - before we got married I knew I was going out - to him. I wasn't going to be left here, no idea of it. And I thought to myself it'll be one way of getting rid of everything. Leave everything behind. Start life afresh. And - we were 
writing for about - six months before things could get going you know, to get - married quarters. And - I think I told you about the other. They examined him. And all that. And I didn't go there, he came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So how long was he away altogether then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 About twelve months. He came back. Came back. They sent him back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 He didn't work much after that did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 No. But I never had a regret with him. Never had one regret. He was a good boy. Was a good boy but didn't have a chance. And that was a
nother thing that made me feel - determined. I worked for me own, because - he had to go - on parish relief. Which we had to do because - having babies and he was - wanted attention all time, he was fastened in bed nearly all the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 What was his illness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 
T.B. Yes. And - it was a real - really shame, it was, he was such a nice big fellow. And he would have made a - you know, we would have meant something, we would, yes. We couldn't have gone wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 How old were your children when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 When he died? The eldest was - five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And how old was the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 And then - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 Stanley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272  was ten months. And a little girl I buried in between you know, she was sixteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5075639\charrsid10098272 She\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 s the one that fell isn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Aye, that one, yes. It was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 So it was a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. And I struggled with the - Jim, and I had a bigger struggle with - the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 But that was a different sort of struggle wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Yes. But - like of all that I've got me children and - the sa
me thing applies now. I'm happier now than I've ever been in me life. I am. Though I never go out anywhere as you know, I don't go out anywhere. Only if the kids insist on taking me, same as Jim did. I'm quite happy go work because - they're nice at work,
 the girls are. Have plenty - you know, laughs and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3276866 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 You're definitely happier now than you've ever been in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4813082 MM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5775726\charrsid10098272 Ever been in me life. It seems a shame you've got work until you're seventy, before you can enjoy life.
